{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17514554","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17514554"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T13:23:34+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T13:23:34+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12330"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"12330","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12330"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.3,0.55,0.08,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4850"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78443"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4850","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4850"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12330"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63805"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"602"},{"type":"tags","id":"655"},{"type":"tags","id":"1167"},{"type":"tags","id":"2560"},{"type":"tags","id":"2778"},{"type":"tags","id":"4974"},{"type":"tags","id":"6189"},{"type":"tags","id":"6523"},{"type":"tags","id":"11633"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"7833"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7968"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26730"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42738"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43318"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78443","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78443"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 50-year-old woman presents with a one week history of a shooting pain in her left knee joint, left medial calf and the anterolateral portion of her thigh. This pain started after she had a fall at home. She also has difficulty in straightening her left leg and a loss of sensation on the medial area of her calf. On examination her ankle reflex is normal but her knee reflex is diminished on her left side and the power in her left quadriceps muscle is also decreased. An MRI shows compression of a lumbosacral nerve root.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely nerve root involved?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["L2","L3","L4","L5","S1"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe patient is presenting with lumbosacral radiculopathy of the \u003Cstrong\u003EL4\u003C/strong\u003E nerve root secondary to nerve root compression due to a traumatic fall. L4 radiculopathy is characterised by a diminished knee reflex, sensory loss on the medial calf, motor loss of quadriceps and thigh adductor muscles and pain distribution on the knee, medial calf and anterolateral thigh. L4 nerve root compression will cause a diminished knee reflex.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EL2\u003C/strong\u003E radiculopathy is characterised by a sensory deficit in the upper anterior thigh, a motor deficit due to a decrease in function of the psoas muscle and pain in the area of the anterior thigh only.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EL3\u003C/strong\u003E radiculopathy is characterised by sensory loss in the lower anterior thigh and knee region, motor deficit due to a decrease in function of the psoas muscle, quadriceps muscle and thigh adductors and pain in the anterior thigh and knee area.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAn \u003Cstrong\u003EL5\u003C/strong\u003E nerve root compression will result in sensory deficit on the lateral calf and dorsal surface of the foot, a motor deficit in the function of peronei, tibialis anterior, gluteus medius and toe dorsiflexors, and pain in the area of lateral calf, dorsal foot, posterolateral thigh and buttocks.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ES1\u003C/strong\u003E nerve root compression will cause a diminished ankle reflex, sensory deficit on the plantar and lateral surface of the foot, and motor loss of the gastrocnemius/soleus, abductor hallucis and gluteus maximus muscles. Pain distribution will be in the area of the posterior calf, the bottom of the foot, posterior thighs and buttocks.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["L4 nerve root compression will cause a diminished knee reflex.","L4 radiculopathy is associated with sensory loss on the medial calf and motor weakness in the quadriceps muscle."],"references":["Alexander CE, Weisbrod LJ, Varacallo MA. Lumbosacral Radiculopathy. 2024 Feb 27. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2025 Jan\u2013. PMID: 28613587. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28613587/","Tarulli AW, Raynor EM. Lumbosacral radiculopathy. Neurol Clin. 2007 May;25(2):387-405. doi: 10.1016/j.ncl.2007.01.008. PMID: 17445735. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17445735/","Berry JA, Elia C, Saini HS, Miulli DE. A Review of Lumbar Radiculopathy, Diagnosis, and Treatment. Cureus. 2019 Oct 17;11(10):e5934. doi: 10.7759/cureus.5934. PMID: 31788391; PMCID: PMC6858271. Available from: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC6858271/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63805"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12330"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63805","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63805"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-10T18:53:26+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-10T18:54:08+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4850"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78443"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com